  , issueTitle = "Check if the connected server is a proxy"
  , issuePullRequest = Nothing
  , issueUrl =
      "https://api.github.com/repos/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/5485"
  , issueCreatedAt = 2016 (-03) (-06) 07 : 04 : 44 UTC
  , issueBody =
      Just
        "**Description**\r\n\r\nCurrently, there is no direct way to determine, whether or not the connected server is a proxy. This is important, because when using configuration in production environments, setting the server name to localhost is a no-go. Instead, we dynamically check if there is a proxy available on localhost.\r\n\r\nHowever, the downside of this is, that if the local server is not a proxy, but a serving rethink server our software will not work as expected (obviously, since it's use the wrong server).\r\n\r\n**Feature Request**\r\n\r\nAn easy solution for us would be to have a simple check, like _server()_ providing an _isProxy_ field:\r\n\r\n`conn.server()` returning `{ \"id\": \"404bef53-4b2c-433f-9184-bc3f7bda4a15\", \"name\": \"amadeus\", \"isProxy\": \"true\" }`\r\n\r\nsee [api docs](https://www.rethinkdb.com/api/javascript/server/).\r\n\r\n**Workaround**\r\n\r\nWhat we're currently doing is simply trying to connect to _localhost_ and check whether or not the expected server is part of the cluster. We do this by having both the _server name_ and the _server id_ in our configuration (pseudo code):\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar conn = r.connect({ host: 'localhost', port: 28015, db: env.mainDb.database });\r\n\r\nif (conn) {\r\n  if (r.db('rethinkdb').table('server_config').getAll(env.mainDb.hostId).isEmpty()) {\r\n    conn.close({ noreplyWait: true });\r\n    conn = null;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nif (!conn) {\r\n  conn = rethinkdb.connect({ host: env.mainDb.hostname, port: 28015, db: env.mainDb.database });\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis trick allows us to automatically check for a local rethinkdb proxy and ensure that it belongs to the correct cluster. If not, it will connect to the server directly, the old way.\r\n"
  , issueState = "closed"
  , issueId = Id 138761694
